This simple plugin is to let Cronos II users to
sign messages with a random signature using the
output of any program.

To compile this program you need Cronos II 0.2.0
at least, which can be downloaded from
http://cronosII.sourceforge.net/

##Please see README in plugins directory ## --pete

The installation process is as follows:
1. Unpack the sources of cronosII-fortune.
2. Change to the directory where the unpacked files were written.
3. Run 'make'
4. Run 'make install' as root.

To use this plugin you should run Cronos II and open
the Preferences dialog, go to the Plug-Ins option,
press the "Load" button and select the file fortune.so

After that you can configure the plugin with the
"Configuration" button.
